	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Sep 26th 9:47 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>680 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All this info is buried somewhere in these boards, but i'll offer the basic differences in a very short nutshell.<br><br>Iksar get infravision, humans don't.<br>Iksar are KOS (Kill on Sight by guards/npcs) most places, Humans are KOS in only a few places.<br>Iksar get regen, humans don't.<br>Iksar start at 100 swimming skill (I believe) but that's not a big deal because swimming is easily trained.<br>Iksar suffer from a 20% experience penalty.<br>At higher levels, human fists are slightly faster thank Iksar fists.<br>Iksar have a very good newb zone.<br>Iksar cannot wear some armor pieces that Humans can, (anything plate) but get the shackle quests as compensation.<br>Iksar get better starting agility - which gives them more AC.<br><br>But, I doubt you'll find many Human Monks who wish they went Iksar, nor will you find many Iksar monks who wish they went Human.&nbsp;&nbsp;Play whichever race you want - it doesn't make any REAL difference if you enjoy the game.<br><br>As for starting stats, it's a big debate.  My opinion is to split them between Str and Sta, and avoid the Agi/Dex trap.  Some will say all Sta, some will say mostly Str.  Not too big a deal.  I wish I had gone Str/Sta, instead of what I did (10 Agi, 4 Str 3 Dex 3 Sta) but I'm doing just fine.<br><br>But, if you're level 5, you can easily restart if you want to.  My personal feeling is that since this is your first time in EQ, and you probably don't have the experience to understand the nuances of faction and the difficulty of travel when you're KOS, go back, start as a Human and put 10 points into Str and 10 points into Sta.  That's my opinion only - others may and probably will differ.  I believe that starting an Iksar as your first character is a tougher road - but if you're into the Iksar thing, go for it.<br><br>Just be prepared for a lot of handbag jokes.  ;)</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
